      • upsert

        public EntityMutationResponse upsert()
                              throws AtlanException
        If an entity with the same qualifiedName exists, updates the existing entity. Otherwise, creates the entity. No classifications or custom metadata will be changed if updating an existing entity, irrespective of what is included in the entity itself when the method is called.
        Returns:
        details of the created or updated entity
        Throws:
        AtlanException - on any error during the API invocation

      • upsert

        public EntityMutationResponse upsert​(boolean replaceClassifications,
                                     boolean replaceCustomMetadata)
                              throws AtlanException
        If no entity exists, has the same behavior as the upsert() method. If an entity does exist, optionally overwrites any classifications and / or custom metadata.
        Parameters:
        replaceClassifications - whether to replace classifications during an update (true) or not (false)
        replaceCustomMetadata - whether to replace custom metadata during an update (true) or not (false)
        Returns:
        details of the created or updated entity
        Throws:
        AtlanException - on any error during the API invocation

        public static Entity retrieveFull​(java.lang.String guid)
                           throws AtlanException

        Parameters:

        Returns:

      • delete

        public static EntityMutationResponse delete​(java.lang.String guid)
                                     throws AtlanException
        Soft-deletes an entity by its GUID. This operation can be reversed by updating the entity and changing its status to ACTIVE.
        Parameters:
        guid - of the entity to soft-delete
        Returns:
        details of the soft-deleted entity
        Throws:
        AtlanException - on any error during the API invocation

      • purge

        public static EntityMutationResponse purge​(java.lang.String guid)
                                    throws AtlanException
        Hard-deletes (purges) an entity by its GUID. This operation is irreversible. The entity to purge must currently be in an active state (soft-deleted entities cannot be purged).
        Parameters:
        guid - of the entity to hard-delete
        Returns:
        details of the hard-deleted entity
        Throws:
        AtlanException - on any error during the API invocation

      • updateCustomMetadataAttributes

        public static void updateCustomMetadataAttributes​(java.lang.String guid,
                                                  java.lang.String cmName,
                                                  CustomMetadataAttributes attributes)
                                           throws AtlanException
        Update only the provided custom metadata attributes on the asset. This will leave all other custom metadata attributes, even within the same named custom metadata, unchanged.
        Parameters:
        guid - unique identifier of the asset
        cmName - human-readable name of the custom metadata to update
        attributes - the values of the custom metadata attributes to change
        Throws:
        AtlanException - on any API problems, or if the custom metadata is not defined in Atlan

      • replaceCustomMetadata

        public static void replaceCustomMetadata​(java.lang.String guid,
                                         java.lang.String cmName,
                                         CustomMetadataAttributes attributes)
                                  throws AtlanException
        Replace specific custom metadata on the asset. This will replace everything within the named custom metadata, but will not change any of the other named custom metadata on the asset.
        Parameters:
        guid - unique identifier of the asset
        cmName - human-readable name of the custom metadata to replace
        attributes - the values of the attributes to replace for the custom metadata
        Throws:
        AtlanException - on any API problems, or if the custom metadata is not defined in Atlan
